DOG BOY: Coalition-engineered canine psi-hunters

Dog Boys are a Coalition States military success story and a moral
horror.  Created through genetic engineering that spliced canine DNA
with human stock, Dog Boys are loyal, perceptive, and physically
powerful.  The Coalition breeds them specifically to track psionic
beings, magic users, and supernatural threats.

Despite their Coalition origins, some Dog Boys break conditioning and
flee to the wilderness or join mercenary groups.  They are often
violently distrusted by Coalition citizens when found outside their
expected role.

ATTRIBUTES (APPROXIMATE RANGES)
  IQ: 4-19   ME: 3-18   MA: 3-18   PS: 9-24 (Supernatural)
  PP: 4-19   PE: 9-24   PB: 3-18   Spd: 8-28

DAMAGE POOL
  SDC: 2d6 x10 (approx 20-120)

SPECIAL ABILITIES
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance
  - Enhanced smell: track by scent up to 300 feet, detect ambushes
  - Enhanced hearing: can hear whispered conversation nearby
  - Enhanced taste: detect poisons in food and drink
  - Thermal vision: see heat signatures in darkness
  - Psionic sensitivity: sense the presence of psychics and magic users

PENALTIES
  - Not OCC eligible, Coalition military training defines the path
  - Coalition loyalty conditioning (may cause conflict when playing
    rogue)
  - Susceptible to sonic-based attacks
  - Widely feared and distrusted outside the Coalition

OCC ELIGIBLE: No, racial abilities replace OCC training.
ALIGNMENT: Any (though Coalition-raised Dog Boys tend toward Scrupulous
or Unprincipled; rogues vary widely).

